FBIS4-17182 "drsov078_e_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Negotiations Reportage on Black Sea Fleet Negotiations Radetskyy, Grachev Meet LD2104121394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1108 GMT 21 Apr 94 LD2104121394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS special correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] [Text] Sevastopol, 21 Apr -- Russian-Ukrainian talks on coordinating matters related to the implementation of the Agreement on the Black Sea Fleet, signed on 15 April in Moscow by Boris Yeltsin and Leonid Kravchuk, are continuing. After private talks between Russian and Ukrainian Defense Ministers Pavel Grachev and Vitaliy Radetskyy, the Russian and Ukrainian delegations have began more general talks at the fleet's headquarters. Vitaliy Radetskyy said to journalists after his personal meeting with the Russian minister that "the dialogue is progressing in a constructive manner." He also said that the Ukrainian Navy base must be stationed in Sevastopol. At the same time he did not rule out that Sevastopol may become the location for the deployment of both the main base of the Russian Black Sea Fleet, and the Ukrainian Navy. The agreement, signed by the presidents of the two countries, mentions a separate deployment of the Black Sea Fleet and the Ukrainian Navy.
